      <td>\(0&lt;|(x,y)-(2,3)|=\sqrt{(x-2)^2 +(y-3)^2}&lt;\delta\) dado que $$0&lt;</td>
      <td>y-3</td>
      <td>=\sqrt{(y-3)^2}\leq\sqrt{(x-2)^2 +(y-3)^2}&lt;\delta$$</td>
